><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tya1665702725016.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tya1665702725016.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tya1665702725016.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tya1665702725016\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      tls ca file | directory\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">On Unix, specify the location of the CA certificate used to validate the LDAP server.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tya1665702725016__topic_d51326e1_d51327e1_d51328e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__p_d51329e1_d51330e1_d51331e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS</code> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls ca file</span> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">tlscafil</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">PemFIle</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__p_d51332e1_d51333e1_d51334e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS</code> { <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code> } <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls ca directory</span> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">tlscadir</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">CaDir</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__section_w3153ab1b5b3_w3154ab1b5_w3155ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__p_d51335e1_d51336e1_d51337e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlscafil=/certicates/certificate_file.pem</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tya1665702725016__section_gjm_wgg_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d648739e107\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tya1665702725016__ul_or2_ygg_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tya1665702725016__li_d24446e1_d24447e1_d24448e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">PemFIle</var>—fully-qualified file\n               name of the CA certificate in PEM format. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tya1665702725016__li_d24449e1_d24450e1_d24451e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">CaDir</var>—directory containing the\n               CA certificates with hashed file names. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tya1665702725016__section_nyx_ygg_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d648739e126\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__p_d51344e1_d51345e1_d51346e1\">On Unix, the CA certificate required to validate the\n            LDAP server may be specified as a PEM file or in a directory of hashed file names.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tya1665702725016__p_d51347e1_d51348e1_d51349e1\">The options <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls ca file</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls ca directory</span> are mutually exclusive. Setting either one\n            implicitly sets <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">tls server validation</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=validate</code> (if it is not specified).</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqn1665702774521.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP over TLS</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ldo1665702725085.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>tls server validation</a><p>Instruct the LDAP connector to connect to the LDAP server using TLS.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532580\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532580\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "tls ca file | directory Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 tls ca file | directory On Unix, specify the location of the CA certificate used to validate the LDAP server. USYS$LDP_PARAMS { = } tls ca file | tlscafil = PemFIle USYS$LDP_PARAMS { = } tls ca directory | tlscadir = CaDir Example: USYS$LDP_PARAMS tlscafil=/certicates/certificate_file.pem Arguments PemFIle —fully-qualified file name of the CA certificate in PEM format. CaDir —directory containing the CA certificates with hashed file names. Description On Unix, the CA certificate required to validate the LDAP server may be specified as a PEM file or in a directory of hashed file names. The options tls ca file and tls ca directory are mutually exclusive. Setting either one implicitly sets tls server validation =validate (if it is not specified). Related Links LDAP over TLS tls server validation Instruct the LDAP connector to connect to the LDAP server using TLS. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}